          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Nvidia <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-08-01-2025-h1-1-stock-fell-over-5-percent" target="_blank">stock fell over 5%</a> on Tuesday, erasing Monday’s 3% gain. Traders sold around 200,000 January $140 call options and up to 700,000 February call contracts. The sell-off started after CEO Jensen Huang’s CES presentation, which disappointed investors. February options volatility shifted, showing bearish sentiment with calls now discounted compared to puts. The chipmaker’s stock closed at $141.35, marking a significant drop after hitting a record high earlier this week.</p>
