          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter:blur(5px);">Damac Group CEO Hussain Sajwani announced a $20 billion <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-08-01-2025-h2-2-us-data-center-investment" target="_blank">US data center investment</a>. Speaking at Mar-a-Lago, Sajwani linked the project to strengthening America’s AI leadership. The first phase spans states like Texas, Ohio, and Arizona. Damac aims to capitalize on its decade-long relationship with Trump, which was originally forged through luxury golf courses in Dubai. While funding specifics remain unclear, Sajwani hinted at further expansion if market conditions align.</p>
